WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:32.365 --> 00:00:34.325 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
So, he's got three of them.

00:00:34.409 --> 00:00:35.452 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 grunts]

00:00:36.494 --> 00:00:40.081 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
Qiongqi, Hundun, and Taotie.

00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.459 position:50% align:center
For Hishigata, who's
not even a necromancer,

00:00:42.542 --> 00:00:44.336 position:50% align:center
to keep using them is dangerous!

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:50.633 position:50% align:center
Leave Hishigata
and Hirumi to me.

00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:53.470 position:50% align:center
They have to be stopped.
All of this...

00:00:53.553 --> 00:00:56.806 position:50% align:center
It only happened because
I came here, to this city.

00:02:38.783 --> 00:02:39.868 position:50% align:center
Huotou.

00:02:39.951 --> 00:02:42.037 position:50% align:center
We're the only ones
who can stop Hirumi.

00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:43.246 position:50% align:center
Let's go!

00:02:43.329 --> 00:02:44.748 position:50% align:center
Acknowledged, Adonai.

00:02:49.085 --> 00:02:51.171 position:50% align:center
Soon we'll be able
to obtain the formula,

00:02:51.254 --> 00:02:53.631 position:50% align:center
and after my Hirumi uses it,
she'll achieve a status

00:02:53.715 --> 00:02:56.051 position:50% align:center
the likes of which
no one has seen before!

00:02:56.134 --> 00:02:58.303 position:50% align:center
Our dream will
finally come true!

00:02:58.386 --> 00:03:00.180 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
That's right, Hirumi!

00:03:00.263 --> 00:03:02.474 position:50% align:center
[HIRUMI] Brother,
what will happen afterwards?

00:03:02.557 --> 00:03:04.809 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Isn't the answer obvious?

00:03:04.893 --> 00:03:06.936 position:50% align:center
Once Academy City sees
the fruits of our labor,

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:09.314 position:50% align:center
they'll have no choice but
to acknowledge our success.

00:03:09.397 --> 00:03:10.857 position:50% align:center
No.

00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:13.234 position:50% align:center
I was talking about when all
of this is over and done with.

00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:15.403 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Oh, you mean that?

00:03:15.487 --> 00:03:16.488 position:50% align:center
Well, let's see.

00:03:16.571 --> 00:03:18.239 position:50% align:center
When morning comes, I'll get up,

00:03:18.323 --> 00:03:19.699 position:50% align:center
and then go to sleep at night.

00:03:19.783 --> 00:03:22.202 position:50% align:center
We'll eat healthy,
home-cooked meals.

00:03:22.285 --> 00:03:23.536 position:50% align:center
From now on, Hirumi,

00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:26.122 position:50% align:center
you and I are going to
live normal, happy lives.

00:03:26.206 --> 00:03:28.667 position:50% align:center
But I'm more curious
about what you want.

00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:30.126 position:50% align:center
[HIRUMI]
All I know is

00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:33.380 position:50% align:center
whatever happens, I want you
there by my side, Brother!

00:03:37.509 --> 00:03:39.386 position:50% align:center
Doesn't this guy ever give up?

00:03:42.847 --> 00:03:43.973 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR laughing]

00:03:47.644 --> 00:03:50.105 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] What's wrong,
Heap of Junk Number One?

00:03:50.188 --> 00:03:51.856 position:50% align:center
You're not getting
tired, are you?

00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:53.108 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.790 position:50% align:center
I'm guessing you're a
little slow to catch on.

00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:13.086 position:50% align:center
Hey, you hear me in there?!

00:04:20.176 --> 00:04:21.553 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
That was a close one.

00:04:21.636 --> 00:04:23.972 position:50% align:center
We've got an error message!

00:04:24.055 --> 00:04:25.473 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
The line's disconnected?

00:04:27.767 --> 00:04:29.019 position:50% align:center
Damn it!

00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:31.813 position:50% align:center
That last mishap
messed everything up!

00:04:31.896 --> 00:04:33.815 position:50% align:center
I feel like I'm losing my mind!

00:04:33.898 --> 00:04:35.358 position:50% align:center
We're so close too!

00:04:35.442 --> 00:04:37.902 position:50% align:center
Right when we've nearly gotten
on our hands on the formula!

00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:38.903 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:38.987 --> 00:04:41.364 position:50% align:center
[HIRUMI]
Please calm down, Brother.

00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:43.450 position:50% align:center
Got a little carried
away, didn't I?

00:04:43.533 --> 00:04:45.285 position:50% align:center
We'll just have to
recover Hundun.

00:04:45.368 --> 00:04:49.372 position:50% align:center
Then transfer the rest of
the formula data via hard-wire.

00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:50.415 position:50% align:center
Hirumi?

00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:52.959 position:50% align:center
I just had the most
brilliant idea.

00:04:57.672 --> 00:04:58.923 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCEMENT 09A]
Due to system interference

00:04:59.007 --> 00:05:00.258 position:50% align:center
with the infrastructure,

00:05:00.342 --> 00:05:02.844 position:50% align:center
Academy City has deemed
School District Sixteen

00:05:02.927 --> 00:05:04.804 position:50% align:center
off-limits.

00:05:04.888 --> 00:05:08.433 position:50% align:center
All those in said district,
evacuate at once. I repeat.

00:05:08.516 --> 00:05:09.601 position:50% align:center
[SECURITY OFFICER 09A]
Keep back!

00:05:09.684 --> 00:05:11.811 position:50% align:center
The area ahead is restricted!

00:05:11.895 --> 00:05:13.021 position:50% align:center
For real?

00:05:13.104 --> 00:05:14.439 position:50% align:center
Then you're not gonna
let us go to school?

00:05:14.522 --> 00:05:16.232 position:50% align:center
Does that mean we get today off?

00:05:21.571 --> 00:05:23.031 position:50% align:center
[CROWD yells]

00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:26.534 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR chuckles]

00:05:26.618 --> 00:05:28.119 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 09C]
Was that a person?

00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:36.002 position:50% align:center
[QIONGQI]
Target Accelerator acquired.

00:05:36.086 --> 00:05:38.171 position:50% align:center
Trajectory calculated.

00:05:38.254 --> 00:05:41.424 position:50% align:center
Disregarding mission
damage to surrounding area.

00:05:41.508 --> 00:05:43.593 position:50% align:center
Data sent to Taotie.

00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:45.553 position:50% align:center
[TAOTIE]
Receiving data from Qiongqi.

00:05:55.897 --> 00:05:57.232 position:50% align:center
Well, what do you think?

00:05:57.315 --> 00:05:58.733 position:50% align:center
You like my idea?

00:05:58.817 --> 00:06:01.319 position:50% align:center
Slow him down rather
than fighting him directly?

00:06:01.403 --> 00:06:02.987 position:50% align:center
Why didn't I think of that?

00:06:05.198 --> 00:06:06.574 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 09D screams]

00:06:08.076 --> 00:06:10.412 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Tch. Imitating others.

00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:11.788 position:50% align:center
How tacky!

00:06:17.877 --> 00:06:19.629 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Hey, Heap of Junk Number Three!

00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.006 position:50% align:center
You dropped this!

00:06:27.429 --> 00:06:30.056 position:50% align:center
That twisted freak
ended up getting away.

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:32.142 position:50% align:center
But after making such
a big scene fleeing.

00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:34.436 position:50% align:center
I can guess which
direction he went.

00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:42.277 position:50% align:center
Tell him something for me!

00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:44.237 position:50% align:center
I'm on my way right now!

00:07:01.755 --> 00:07:03.214 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Mmm. It's true!

00:07:03.298 --> 00:07:06.760 position:50% align:center
Downloading information
over cables is much faster!

00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:08.720 position:50% align:center
We're up to 95%.

00:07:08.803 --> 00:07:11.890 position:50% align:center
There's 97... 99...

00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.275 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Accelerator!

00:07:23.818 --> 00:07:24.986 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Hmm?

00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:01.981 position:50% align:center
"So it was you," says Misaka,

00:08:02.065 --> 00:08:04.734 position:50% align:center
recognizing the face of
the person who saved her,

00:08:04.818 --> 00:08:07.612 position:50% align:center
as surprise appears on her own.

00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:09.823 position:50% align:center
[LAST ORDER gasps]
"Welcome back!"

00:08:09.906 --> 00:08:12.283 position:50% align:center
says Misaka Misaka,
sensing your presence

00:08:12.367 --> 00:08:13.910 position:50% align:center
and springing awake!

00:08:16.746 --> 00:08:17.747 position:50% align:center
He's gone.

00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:20.333 position:50% align:center
Was I just... dreaming?

00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:23.962 position:50% align:center
Aww.

00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:26.464 position:50% align:center
"Ugh. I'm so
unbelievably bored,"

00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:28.925 position:50% align:center
mutters Misaka
Misaka, unhappily.

00:08:33.805 --> 00:08:35.056 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Huh?

00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:37.934 position:50% align:center
Bravo. You truly are
the first-ranked.

00:08:41.229 --> 00:08:42.897 position:50% align:center
I recognize that voice.

00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:44.274 position:50% align:center
From the first
moment I heard it,

00:08:44.357 --> 00:08:46.151 position:50% align:center
it made me feel
sick to my stomach.

00:08:46.234 --> 00:08:48.653 position:50% align:center
Now I can say the
same about your face.

00:08:48.737 --> 00:08:50.030 position:50% align:center
I don't like this guy.

00:08:50.113 --> 00:08:53.074 position:50% align:center
Now, now, hear me out
before you overreact.

00:08:53.158 --> 00:08:54.617 position:50% align:center
You've arrived at the best part!

00:08:54.701 --> 00:08:56.828 position:50% align:center
Do you know the extent
of my research over the

00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:58.538 position:50% align:center
last few years?

00:08:58.621 --> 00:09:00.498 position:50% align:center
The espers aboard
Qiongqi and Taotie,

00:09:00.582 --> 00:09:03.918 position:50% align:center
which you easily defeated,
were originally Level Three!

00:09:04.002 --> 00:09:05.587 position:50% align:center
But with my esper
boosting paired

00:09:05.670 --> 00:09:07.130 position:50% align:center
with Esther's pseudo-souls,

00:09:07.213 --> 00:09:09.674 position:50% align:center
their abilities were raised
all the way to Level Five!

00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:11.259 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:09:11.343 --> 00:09:14.304 position:50% align:center
And yet, they still were
no match for you.

00:09:14.387 --> 00:09:16.139 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Are you an idiot or something?

00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:17.891 position:50% align:center
If you hook junk
up to more junk,

00:09:17.974 --> 00:09:19.476 position:50% align:center
you still end up with junk.

00:09:19.559 --> 00:09:20.977 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA laughs]

00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:24.022 position:50% align:center
You'd've been right.
Until recently.

00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:26.274 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
What's that supposed to mean?

00:09:26.358 --> 00:09:27.859 position:50% align:center
After everything
you've thrown my way,

00:09:27.942 --> 00:09:31.112 position:50% align:center
you think you can gain even a
millimeter of victory over me?

00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:32.614 position:50% align:center
Well, you see...

00:09:32.697 --> 00:09:36.284 position:50% align:center
Now I have the memories of
10,031 deaths I got from her.

00:09:36.368 --> 00:09:38.328 position:50% align:center
When I install my
formula into those three,

00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:39.996 position:50% align:center
you'll finally get your wish.

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:41.456 position:50% align:center
Enemies worth fighting,
or rather

00:09:41.539 --> 00:09:42.999 position:50% align:center
ones you can
kneel before.

00:09:43.083 --> 00:09:45.710 position:50% align:center
Opponents you'd write out as
"nemesis," but read as "friend."

00:09:45.794 --> 00:09:46.920 position:50% align:center
Watch.

00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:48.546 position:50% align:center
With one press of this button...

00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:50.674 position:50% align:center
That won't be necessary.

00:09:50.757 --> 00:09:52.342 position:50% align:center
You've caused me
enough trouble already

00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:54.928 position:50% align:center
with all of your pathetic
attempts at darkness.

00:09:55.011 --> 00:09:57.263 position:50% align:center
What have you done?!

00:09:57.347 --> 00:09:59.933 position:50% align:center
You've completely
destroyed our dream!

00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:01.976 position:50% align:center
[crying]

00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:05.188 position:50% align:center
Looks like all it took to snap
your brain was a little despair.

00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:08.692 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA crying]

00:10:08.775 --> 00:10:10.443 position:50% align:center
I was only kidding.

00:10:10.527 --> 00:10:13.697 position:50% align:center
Actually, it's already
been installed.

00:10:13.780 --> 00:10:15.740 position:50% align:center
That's right, mmm!

00:10:15.824 --> 00:10:17.367 position:50% align:center
It's up and running!

00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:19.619 position:50% align:center
[chuckling]

00:10:19.703 --> 00:10:21.621 position:50% align:center
I'll admit, at first,
when you arrived,

00:10:21.705 --> 00:10:24.416 position:50% align:center
I was feeling slightly
anxious inside.

00:10:24.499 --> 00:10:26.751 position:50% align:center
You really are
a genius, Brother!

00:10:26.835 --> 00:10:28.420 position:50% align:center
Yeah.
I'd say it's just about time

00:10:28.503 --> 00:10:30.088 position:50% align:center
for them to be restarted.

00:10:41.307 --> 00:10:42.642 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
We'll leave him to you.

00:10:42.726 --> 00:10:44.394 position:50% align:center
We should get moving, Brother.

00:10:44.477 --> 00:10:46.938 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] Mmm.
After one last fine-tuning.

00:10:47.022 --> 00:10:48.064 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Huh?

00:10:48.148 --> 00:10:50.525 position:50% align:center
The formula was
designed for Hirumi.

00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:52.652 position:50% align:center
Once installed,
she will attain perfection

00:10:52.736 --> 00:10:55.405 position:50% align:center
and become an absolute
esper, a Level Six.

00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:56.406 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:10:56.489 --> 00:10:58.116 position:50% align:center
Meaning she'll surpass you.

00:10:58.199 --> 00:11:00.368 position:50% align:center
Yeah? Go ahead
and keep dreaming.

00:11:09.127 --> 00:11:11.504 position:50% align:center
Get out of my way,
you bucket of bolts.

00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:22.390 position:50% align:center
Get out of here right now.

00:11:22.474 --> 00:11:23.350 position:50% align:center
But I...

00:11:23.433 --> 00:11:24.517 position:50% align:center
Beat it!

00:11:26.478 --> 00:11:28.355 position:50% align:center
Misaka wanted to
fight alongside you,

00:11:28.438 --> 00:11:30.106 position:50% align:center
but now is worried
about being a bother

00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:32.359 position:50% align:center
and has decided to
give you some distance.

00:11:32.442 --> 00:11:34.861 position:50% align:center
Nobody ever asked
you to be considerate.

00:11:34.944 --> 00:11:38.323 position:50% align:center
Don't forget about the damage
I inflicted on all of you.

00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:40.450 position:50% align:center
Just keep quiet and
hold it against me.

00:11:42.452 --> 00:11:44.496 position:50% align:center
Now that the baggage
has been recovered,

00:11:44.579 --> 00:11:46.873 position:50% align:center
there's only one
thing left to do.

00:11:46.956 --> 00:11:48.625 position:50% align:center
Tear you into pieces!

00:11:54.673 --> 00:11:56.049 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR yells]

00:11:56.132 --> 00:11:58.093 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 gasps]
He's gone.

00:11:58.176 --> 00:12:00.011 position:50% align:center
No... They've removed him!

00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:11.439 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Asportation, huh?

00:12:23.868 --> 00:12:25.245 position:50% align:center
--[MISAKA 10046 gasps]
--[HISHIGATA chuckles]

00:12:25.328 --> 00:12:27.580 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] I'll bet that
was pretty surprising, huh?

00:12:27.664 --> 00:12:30.542 position:50% align:center
Mmm, disappearing
right before your eyes.

00:12:30.625 --> 00:12:34.462 position:50% align:center
It's a new ability Taotie
acquired, thanks to my formula.

00:12:34.546 --> 00:12:37.090 position:50% align:center
It also allows the evolved
Taotie and Qiongqi

00:12:37.173 --> 00:12:38.842 position:50% align:center
to link with each
other's vision.

00:12:41.594 --> 00:12:44.222 position:50% align:center
Whatever Qiongqi's
camera captures...

00:12:44.305 --> 00:12:45.890 position:50% align:center
[TAOTIE]
Target acquired.

00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:48.393 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] ...gets shared with
Taotie in a remote location,

00:12:48.476 --> 00:12:51.354 position:50% align:center
allowing him to be
projected there.

00:12:51.438 --> 00:12:53.606 position:50% align:center
Thus concludes my spoiler.

00:12:53.690 --> 00:12:57.193 position:50% align:center
But describing it doesn't
do it justice. Mmm.

00:12:57.277 --> 00:12:58.737 position:50% align:center
And that's not all.

00:13:00.822 --> 00:13:02.282 position:50% align:center
[TAOTIE]
Qiongqi identified.

00:13:04.034 --> 00:13:05.660 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 gasps]

00:13:05.744 --> 00:13:07.454 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
By sharing vision with Taotie,

00:13:07.537 --> 00:13:10.290 position:50% align:center
the impossible becomes reality.

00:13:10.373 --> 00:13:13.209 position:50% align:center
Combine my coffin's
ability-boosting power,

00:13:13.293 --> 00:13:16.004 position:50% align:center
the Si-xiong talismans
I stole from Esther,

00:13:16.087 --> 00:13:18.048 position:50% align:center
and top it off with the formula,

00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:21.760 position:50% align:center
and I've made Qiongqi
and Taotie invincible!

00:13:21.843 --> 00:13:24.346 position:50% align:center
Oh, how the first-ranked
is going to die!

00:13:24.429 --> 00:13:27.474 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 panting]

00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:29.893 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] The body inside
Taotie possessed just a humble

00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:33.021 position:50% align:center
transportation ability,
allowing her to trade places

00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:35.648 position:50% align:center
with her favorite
stuffed animal.

00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:38.985 position:50% align:center
And now, look at the kind
of power it's become, mmm!

00:13:39.069 --> 00:13:40.779 position:50% align:center
Hey, are you listening?

00:13:45.075 --> 00:13:47.911 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] Mmm, everything
is nearly complete.

00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:50.789 position:50% align:center
When you awaken,
you'll be a Level Six.

00:13:50.872 --> 00:13:52.665 position:50% align:center
I'm grateful.

00:13:52.749 --> 00:13:55.794 position:50% align:center
For everything that you've
done for me, Brother.

00:13:55.877 --> 00:13:57.837 position:50% align:center
It wasn't just for you.

00:13:57.921 --> 00:13:59.589 position:50% align:center
This was about both of us.

00:13:59.673 --> 00:14:02.842 position:50% align:center
Right. No one else matters.

00:14:02.926 --> 00:14:05.470 position:50% align:center
Once this is over, I'm thinking
we should pay a visit

00:14:05.553 --> 00:14:07.222 position:50% align:center
to your gym.

00:14:07.305 --> 00:14:08.556 position:50% align:center
I'll tag along.

00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:14.813 position:50% align:center
What's the matter?
Don't you wanna go?

00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:18.775 position:50% align:center
Of course.

00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:21.027 position:50% align:center
If you're there!

00:14:21.111 --> 00:14:22.904 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Okay. Ready to start?

00:14:22.987 --> 00:14:24.072 position:50% align:center
[HIRUMI]
Mm-hmm.

00:14:42.215 --> 00:14:44.175 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
You listening, Trash Lord?

00:14:44.259 --> 00:14:46.553 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna destroy these
two rust buckets real quick,

00:14:46.636 --> 00:14:48.054 position:50% align:center
then head your way.

00:14:48.138 --> 00:14:49.848 position:50% align:center
I figure when I finish, you
should have had long enough

00:14:49.931 --> 00:14:52.142 position:50% align:center
for your life to flash
before your eyes.

00:14:52.225 --> 00:14:55.061 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] I can't have you
coming here anytime soon.

00:14:55.145 --> 00:14:57.522 position:50% align:center
Not when the second round
is just beginning.

00:14:57.605 --> 00:15:00.066 position:50% align:center
Really? Who do you think
you're talking to?

00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:01.943 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Okay, let's begin.

00:15:12.287 --> 00:15:13.621 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Surprised, mmm?

00:15:13.705 --> 00:15:15.331 position:50% align:center
That's the formula at work.

00:15:15.415 --> 00:15:17.334 position:50% align:center
A boosted version
of Replace, huh?

00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:18.752 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Mmm, correct.

00:15:20.045 --> 00:15:21.171 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 gasps]

00:15:26.176 --> 00:15:30.055 position:50% align:center
"I see, that's how my memories
enhanced Taotie and Qiongqi,"

00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:31.931 position:50% align:center
says Misaka, bewildered.

00:15:36.311 --> 00:15:37.395 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR grunts]

00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:44.444 position:50% align:center
But, without a
weapon of her own,

00:15:44.527 --> 00:15:47.405 position:50% align:center
she can only grit her teeth
and watch in dismay.

00:15:58.667 --> 00:16:00.960 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER panting]

00:16:01.044 --> 00:16:02.128 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 grunts]

00:16:04.172 --> 00:16:05.674 position:50% align:center
How did you get away?

00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:10.261 position:50% align:center
Master!

00:16:10.345 --> 00:16:12.472 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046] "Master?" Misaka
asks, wondering what you mean.

00:16:12.555 --> 00:16:14.933 position:50% align:center
I mean Accelerator,
he's my master!

00:16:15.016 --> 00:16:17.185 position:50% align:center
Where's Hishigata,
the one who captured you?

00:16:17.268 --> 00:16:20.105 position:50% align:center
I have to defeat him if I'm
going to help out my master!

00:16:26.945 --> 00:16:28.697 position:50% align:center
Only 20% left to go.

00:16:28.780 --> 00:16:29.864 position:50% align:center
[beeping]

00:16:29.948 --> 00:16:32.200 position:50% align:center
Huh? Damn! What now?!

00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.375 position:50% align:center
It's Hundun.

00:16:47.882 --> 00:16:49.467 position:50% align:center
Danger to Adonai detected.

00:16:49.551 --> 00:16:52.345 position:50% align:center
Executing action to eliminate
the enemy threat.

00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:53.930 position:50% align:center
After all this time apart,

00:16:54.014 --> 00:16:56.433 position:50% align:center
you dare to come
back now, Esther?

00:16:56.516 --> 00:16:57.559 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
That's right!

00:16:57.642 --> 00:16:59.894 position:50% align:center
I'm here to keep my
promise to Hirumi!

00:16:59.978 --> 00:17:02.731 position:50% align:center
That thing walking around in
her skin is actually Taowu,

00:17:02.814 --> 00:17:04.524 position:50% align:center
one of the Evil Spirits
of the Numbers!

00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:06.985 position:50% align:center
Instead of worrying about
what you can't control,

00:17:07.068 --> 00:17:10.155 position:50% align:center
sit back and enjoy
the fruits of our labor.

00:17:10.238 --> 00:17:12.282 position:50% align:center
Hundun, if you'd be so kind?

00:17:18.788 --> 00:17:21.416 position:50% align:center
Hey, third-string!
Didn't even scratch me!

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:32.802 position:50% align:center
So that's what they were up to?

00:17:43.980 --> 00:17:45.023 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR grunts]

00:17:51.279 --> 00:17:53.740 position:50% align:center
I need to smash the junkpile
that's popping objects

00:17:53.823 --> 00:17:54.991 position:50% align:center
in and out.

00:17:57.494 --> 00:18:00.747 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR laughing]

00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:02.832 position:50% align:center
[laughing continues]

00:18:19.099 --> 00:18:21.434 position:50% align:center
Not yet! Still too soon!

00:18:21.518 --> 00:18:25.230 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:18:25.313 --> 00:18:27.357 position:50% align:center
Now's it's time
to bust you open!

00:18:29.484 --> 00:18:31.236 position:50% align:center
"Unbelievable.

00:18:31.319 --> 00:18:34.239 position:50% align:center
He's taking the friction
of the sand colliding

00:18:34.322 --> 00:18:37.534 position:50% align:center
and releasing the heat all
at once to ignite the debris."

00:18:37.617 --> 00:18:40.412 position:50% align:center
"It's like a whirlwind
of fire," says Misaka,

00:18:40.495 --> 00:18:42.288 position:50% align:center
mumbling to herself.

00:18:42.372 --> 00:18:44.666 position:50% align:center
"The objective
is Taotie's sight.

00:18:44.749 --> 00:18:47.002 position:50% align:center
By destroying the camera,
he can shut down

00:18:47.085 --> 00:18:49.379 position:50% align:center
their enhanced Replace,"
says Misaka,

00:18:49.462 --> 00:18:51.214 position:50% align:center
again mumbling to herself.

00:19:00.265 --> 00:19:02.017 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] Now that
your camera's destroyed,

00:19:02.100 --> 00:19:03.518 position:50% align:center
you can't see anything.

00:19:10.734 --> 00:19:13.862 position:50% align:center
The only question is how to
finish off this remaining one.

00:19:26.875 --> 00:19:29.002 position:50% align:center
Gotta say, that was terrific!

00:19:29.085 --> 00:19:30.962 position:50% align:center
You've given me
plenty to work with!

00:19:32.589 --> 00:19:34.883 position:50% align:center
Care for heap of
junk shish kabobs?

00:20:03.328 --> 00:20:06.122 position:50% align:center
Pissants like you ought to
know when to call it quits.

00:20:06.206 --> 00:20:08.917 position:50% align:center
Still, I gotta respect that
you never stopped struggling.

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:10.710 position:50% align:center
Right to the very end.

00:20:14.756 --> 00:20:17.509 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 panting]

00:20:29.062 --> 00:20:32.148 position:50% align:center
[footsteps]

00:20:32.232 --> 00:20:34.776 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] I expected no
less from the first-ranked.

00:20:34.859 --> 00:20:36.611 position:50% align:center
Taking out Taotie and Qiongqi,

00:20:36.695 --> 00:20:39.781 position:50% align:center
even with the formula installed,
was a piece of cake for you.

00:20:39.864 --> 00:20:42.158 position:50% align:center
So much for their new abilities.

00:20:42.242 --> 00:20:44.369 position:50% align:center
I was hoping they'd
prove more entertaining.

00:20:44.452 --> 00:20:46.204 position:50% align:center
But don't think
I'm disappointed.

00:20:46.287 --> 00:20:48.707 position:50% align:center
Those two afforded me
the perfect distraction.

00:20:48.790 --> 00:20:50.542 position:50% align:center
See, while you were
chasing them around,

00:20:50.625 --> 00:20:53.628 position:50% align:center
they bought me enough time
to make my Hirumi perfect.

00:20:54.879 --> 00:20:55.880 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Tch.

00:20:58.091 --> 00:20:59.426 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
No point rushing.

00:20:59.509 --> 00:21:02.095 position:50% align:center
You're too late.
The countdown's already begun.

00:21:03.596 --> 00:21:06.266 position:50% align:center
Just who exactly do you
think you're talking to?

00:21:06.349 --> 00:21:07.976 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] Doesn't matter
what shortcuts you take

00:21:08.059 --> 00:21:10.353 position:50% align:center
with your powers.
You won't make it in time!

00:21:20.989 --> 00:21:22.699 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Not bad at all!

00:21:22.782 --> 00:21:24.909 position:50% align:center
But you won't make it
in time either!

00:21:24.993 --> 00:21:28.163 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:21:28.246 --> 00:21:30.165 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
As head of the Rosenthal family,

00:21:30.248 --> 00:21:33.752 position:50% align:center
I can't allow him to get
away with this anymore.

00:21:33.835 --> 00:21:35.628 position:50% align:center
I need to stab Taowu.

00:21:35.712 --> 00:21:37.547 position:50% align:center
By using Emperor Shun's Blade,

00:21:37.630 --> 00:21:41.009 position:50% align:center
I'll be able to separate the
pseudo-soul from Hirumi's body.

00:21:42.093 --> 00:21:43.762 position:50% align:center
That's not the real Hirumi.

00:21:43.845 --> 00:21:45.513 position:50% align:center
She's no longer in this world.

00:21:47.015 --> 00:21:49.184 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Ninety-eight percent.

00:21:49.267 --> 00:21:50.310 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER gasps]

00:21:53.688 --> 00:21:55.940 position:50% align:center
--[ESTHER] Hirumi!
--[HISHIGATA] 99%!

00:21:57.192 --> 00:21:58.943 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER yelling]

00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:00.528 position:50% align:center
I won't let you!

00:22:12.707 --> 00:22:14.959 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Look what you did, you murderer!

00:22:23.259 --> 00:22:24.844 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Too bad for you, Esther.

00:22:24.928 --> 00:22:27.639 position:50% align:center
Afraid you weren't fast
enough to stop the process.

00:22:27.722 --> 00:22:31.184 position:50% align:center
Behold, this is
a Level Six. Mmm.